      <abstract>Harold Green was a Mount Clemens, Michigan, optometrist who served with the U.S. Army 339th Medical Detachment during the 
American intervention at Archangel, Russia. This collection contains a typescript copy of his diary, containing generally brief entries 
describing his actions in Russia.
</abstract>
